The skinny, tight elastic band that cuts off your mid-section was always creating, for lack of a better term, a small “muffin-top” where one didn’t previously exist. The sisters were living in New York City together where tights were a daily staple for their corporate jobs. Ever resourceful, older sister Ilissa began cutting the elastic off the top of her tights to avoid the digging and pinching (which occurs whether you are a size 2 or a size 18). Dori, always following the lead of her (usually) wiser and older sister followed in suite. One fateful Thanksgiving dinner, she ended up cutting off too much elastic and was left yanking up her tights all night.

Description: nKoso facilitates a fund that focuses on providing primary education for children living in developing countries.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Fund education for students in developing countries that otherwise cannot afford a primary education.  nKoso is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization that leverages the financial power of the crowd to pay tuition fees to affordable private schools. The public education system in many developing countries cannot support the sheer quantity of students. Low-fee private schools are a popular option as they provide more staff accountability, access to technology, and organized curriculum.  The first round of fund raising began on April 15, 2013 in Dormaa Ahenkro Ghana. Partnered with two schools in the region, nKoso accepted 18 students who qualified for financial support for the upcoming school year. Each student on average required $100-$175 USD for a year of education. Within 48 hours of launch all 18 students were fully funded by over 100 donors.  Since launch two more schools in the region have submitted applications for acceptance, and student applications are rolling. nKoso plans to continue it's efforts in Ghana for the remainder of the month. At which point they will move into regions of India and Haiti that support a similar charter school model.
Founders: Anna Owusu, Ben Blodgett, Sylvester Owusu

Description: Give an Awesome is a positive content creation/ sharing tool. Every time you make just one person feel Awesome the World is a better place.
Full Description: Give an Awesome is a content creation tool and social networking platform for positivity. “Have an awesome day!” – is now more than just a cheery phrase, it’s a cool new app designed to spread joy to friends and family to brighten their day.  Give an Awesome, available for free in the App Store, makes it easy to impact someone’s day with a positive surprise and make them smile.  Within seconds, they can share the good tidings by sending it directly to the recipient or by posting it across all of their favorite social media platforms with a single click.  Give An Awesome was developed by The Awesome Company. Give An Awesome has the power to reward someone with a generous dose of goodness.  It’s the electronic version of a spontaneous hug, a pat on the back, or a surprise note in a lunchbox.  By sending someone an “Awesome,” it not only makes the recipient feel good, but it makes the sender feel great too.  After all, isn’t it always better to give than receive?  With this delightful app, everyone wins!   “There is power in the words we use, and we happen to believe that ‘awesome’ is one of the most powerful words on the planet,” explains Give An Awesome co-producer Bert Pope.  “It has the ability to change the world for the better by shifting someone’s energy towards the positive.  Give An Awesome is an affirmation engine for your pocket!” Give An Awesome offers dozens of editing options including filters, logos and graphics.  The expressive app allows a full range of different text styles, sizes and colors for unlimited creativity.  But, if the user doesn’t have the right photo or just isn’t feeling inspired, the app includes plenty of pre-made Awesomes for all occasions, including holiday, birthday, or just because. Please visit the App Store to download Give an Awesome today.

Whereas historically, advertisement has been the only way for users of the Web 2?0 to earn some income for the content they provide online, Netcipia enables every professional or expert-amateur to use the power of Web 2.0 participatory features to build, expand and manage participative communities as well as charge for valuable content. In exchange for this service, there are not fixed costs, Netcipia will only charge a percentage for every transaction. Consultants, teachers, gardeners, architects and so on can use their Netcipia participative communities as a lucrative business tool, using one or several of the three payment models available. Netcipia therefore offers a Win/Win proposition: Users can benefit from the Netcipia platform free of charge to build their community and offer their content worldwide, until they are able to generate some income by monetizing their content through the use of the Netcipia online expertise monetization platform.

Description: A social commerce platform for the expectant and/or new parent(s) that strive to help them discover, test and purchase products.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: A social commerce platform for the expectant and/or new parent(s) that strive to help them discover, test and purchase the most appropriate products for themselves, their babies and their environment while creating a trusted community in which they can learn, develop, and share. Time and sleep starved parents are drawn to the convenience of being able to shop anytime they wish without leaving the family home. We will offer consumers education and products tailored to their unique needs via our website and monthly delivery service. Members of our subscription service will receive a monthly box of curated products to help them discover new and relevant items that coincide with their changing lifestyle. We will source and sell products based on the phase of the parent along with the child’s age, gender and developmental stage. Market research shows increasing health awareness over the years is causing the organic/natural market to rise as people are becoming more and more concerned about the ingredients they put onto and into their bodies. This is especially true as it relates to babies and children. We will research organic and eco-friendly brands in order to deliver quality product choices that in part can be sampled before making a larger initial investment. This “try before you buy” approach will help families make more informed buying decisions. Once products have been proven to work we also provide the simplicity to purchase them directly through our website. In addition, our website will provide helpful content, tools and guidelines that will be fresh and relevant as well as a platform for parents to network and facilitate trades, swaps and sales of samples and other products that they are not interested in or no longer need. Our goal is to infuse convenience, fun, time and cost savings back into the lives of our subscribers.
